<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <meta name="csrf-token" content="<%= csrfToken %>" />
    <title>Learning Management System</title>
    <style>
      body {
        font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
        background-color: #f5f5f5;
        color: #333;
        margin: 0;
        padding: 0;
      }

      .container {
        max-width: 800px;
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 20px;
        background-color: #fff;
        border-radius: 8px;
        box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
      }

      p {
        line-height: 1.6;
        margin-bottom: 10px;
      }
    </style>
  </head>

  <body>
    <div class="container">
      <p>
        The learning management system is developed using Node.js, Express.js,
        Sequelize, and Passport.js for authentication. It serves both students
        and educators, distinguishing them by roles. Educators have the
        privilege to create courses, chapters, and pages, while students can
        enroll in courses and access content.
      </p>
      <p>
        The platform puts emphasis on user-friendliness, allowing users to
        conveniently update passwords on their dashboard and sign out from any
        location.
      </p>
      <p>
        Security and reliability are paramount in the system design, along with
        features aiding in progress tracking and achieving educational
        objectives.
      </p>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>
